1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,680
Where is Lena?

2
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,160
I'm right here.

3
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,400
And if Mr. Tarn had nothing
to do with this,

4
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:00,280
do you know who was really behind it?

5
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:02,120
Go tell your men.

6
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:05,040
How the hell did you let her run away?!

7
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:12,200
<i>Mr. Wayu, the owner</i>
<i>of this house, is a stalker?</i>

8
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:14,960
I should thank Mr. Wayu

9
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:18,080
for risking himself to help me.

10
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,080
If I turn this around…

11
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,280
I want the reward you promised.

12
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,920
I'm a man of my word.

13
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,120
<i>Are you sure?</i>

14
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:35,400
If it's not him, then fine.

15
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,520
<i>Reporters love hyping him up anyway.</i>

16
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,920
What's going on out there?

17
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:43,440
An audio clip the Mad Dog page released.

18
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,160
<i>As for that Mad Dog page</i>

19
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:47,880
<i>exposing Peeraka's case, just set him up.</i>

20
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,920
It's not real.

21
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,160
It must be fake.

22
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:03,520
Fahsai,

23
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,920
go to the foundation first.

24
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,640
Jon, take her out through the back.

25
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,240
- Yes, sir.
- Dad,

26
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,400
something this serious happened
and you want me to go to work?

27
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,920
Your brother and I

28
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,760
need to find the people behind this.

29
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:21,480
Don't worry. They can't do anything to us.

30
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,480
- Jon.
- Yes, sir.

31
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,760
Miss, this way, please.

32
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,240
Knight.

33
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,160
Yes.

34
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,360
Take Miss Fahsai.

35
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,800
<i>Between siblings and what's right,</i>

36
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,520
<i>if you had to choose,</i>
<i>which would you choose?</i>

37
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,640
And beyond siblings,

38
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,880
do you still have justice left
for other people?

39
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,080
Whose cars are these?

40
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,600
Whose cars are these?

41
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,440
Who's that?

42
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,120
I don't know.

43
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,760
Whose cars?

44
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:24,760
I don't know.

45
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,000
Me neither.

46
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,720
Oh.

47
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,680
That's Mr. Chaichana's son.

48
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,720
What is he doing here?

49
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:41,360
I have evidence that all of you reporters
will be interested in

50
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:43,040
regarding that audio clip.

51
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,680
- Oh?
- What is it?

52
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:46,760
What evidence?

53
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:47,720
Yeah.

54
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,600
What's going on here?

55
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,040
- Mr. Mahasamut.
- Mr. Mahasamut.

56
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:54,120
So that is your voice on the clip,
Mr. Mahasamut?

57
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,800
- Is it?
- Is it yours?

58
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:58,280
I can assure you,
that is absolutely not my voice.

59
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,560
I have a way to prove it.

60
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,080
- How?
- What way?

61
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,120
How can you prove it?

62
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:10,480
What right do you have
to verify this audio clip?

63
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,200
Right.

64
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,240
Go ahead.

65
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,280
If you really have a way to prove it.

66
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,600
Sam.

67
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,160
What is it?

68
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:31,480
The clip everyone heard and believes

69
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:34,480
to be Mr. Mahasamut's voice is this one.

70
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:40,880
<i>As for that Mad Dog page</i>
<i>exposing Peeraka's case,</i>

71
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:44,640
<i>it's probably Tarn</i>
<i>or someone in his party.</i>

72
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,960
<i>Are you sure?</i>

73
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:49,520
<i>If it's not him, then fine.</i>

74
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,040
<i>Reporters love hyping him up anyway,</i>

75
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:55,400
<i>calling him the idol</i>
<i>of the new generation.</i>

76
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,600
<i>Just set him up.</i>

77
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,720
Huh?

78
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,240
- It's the same.
- Whose voice is that?

79
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:03,200
But in reality, the tone
and speech pattern in that clip

80
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,640
are not Mr. Mahasamut's.

81
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:06,880
Oh.

82
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:10,480
Oh? Not Mr. Mahasamut's voice?
Then whose voice is it?

83
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,520
That's the same voice.

84
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,920
Yeah.

85
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,080
It's the voice of someone
very similar to him.

86
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,800
But it sounds exactly like him.

87
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,720
Then listen to this.

88
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:27,600
<i>I'm Mahasamut, one of the new-generation</i>
<i>MPs of Namchat Thai Party.</i>

89
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:30,560
<i>I will represent the new generation</i>

90
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:33,480
<i>and lead this country through the crisis.</i>

91
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,040
Sounds familiar?

92
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,560
That's clearly Mr. Mahasamut's voice.

93
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,520
Exactly.

94
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,320
Oh?

95
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,080
So?

96
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:45,400
I'd like all of you
to look at this program.

97
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:49,080
These are the graphs from both clips.

98
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:53,040
You can see that the leaked clip

99
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,840
has a slightly higher pitch
than Mr. Mahasamut's real voice.

100
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:58,480
Without software analysis,

101
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,680
you wouldn't notice
which one is Mr. Mahasamut's voice.

102
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:05,040
But they're different sentences.

103
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,440
Couldn't that affect the tone?

104
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,840
Then let's have Mr. Mahasamut

105
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,600
record the exact same sentence
for comparison

106
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,600
and see if it's different.

107
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,760
Yes, that's perfect.

108
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:16,520
- That's good.
- Right.

109
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,600
That's good.

110
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:20,320
Then we can see whether it's real or not.

111
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,240
Please.

112
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,160
Fine.

113
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,920
I'll do it,

114
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,240
so everyone can be certain.

115
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,000
- Good.
- That's good.

116
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,240
What do I have to say?

117
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,480
You're very kind.

118
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,400
Like I said,

119
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:53,720
I'm happy to help
if there's anything I can do.

120
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,520
Good.

121
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,840
It's great to have
capable people working with us.

122
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,320
Let's be straightforward.

123
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:17,440
You helped us this much.
What do you want in return?

124
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:33,160
I didn't expect the son
of a Thonburi mafia

125
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:36,320
to lower himself
to be a bodyguard for an actress.

126
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:42,840
For that piece of land, I'm willing to.

127
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,480
I hope you're not planning
to speculate on it.

128
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,600
Minister, you're as sharp
as your reputation.

129
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:58,240
I want that land
to open a casino in the city

130
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,400
to support your party's policy
of legal gambling.

131
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:08,400
That's a forward-thinking mindset
for someone of the new generation.

132
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:12,560
Your father would be proud of you.

133
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:16,840
Mr. Samut, you must be proud
of your father too

134
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:21,520
for having such a far-reaching vision.

135
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:27,760
He's doing what others
wouldn't even dare think of.

136
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,720
I'll take my leave.

137
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:38,480
It's an honor to be escorted by you both.

138
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,320
Excuse me.

139
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,920
Why did you let him work with us?

140
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:59,280
We could've repaid him another way.

141
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,360
He's done more in a short time

142
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:05,280
than people who've been here for years.

143
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:12,840
I don't think he'd lower himself
to be Maysa's bodyguard.

144
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,640
Can't you see?

145
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:22,240
He wants that land badly.

146
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,520
Someone born into gambling,

147
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,280
what else could he possibly do?

148
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,800
Cheers!

149
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:41,640
Mahasamut definitely wouldn't expect

150
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:45,440
that you'd outplay him
and work your way into his territory.

151
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:49,000
At first, I thought
you were actually going to help him.

152
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:53,760
But in a way, we still are helping them.

153
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,840
People still don't know
how evil they really are.

154
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:59,800
We have to overlook their small sins first

155
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:03,120
if we want proof of everything.

156
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,760
Small pieces won't fill you up.

157
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,520
You need big ones.

158
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:21,560
With something like this,
you need patience.

159
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,480
Pud,

160
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,280
do you want some corn?

161
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,200
Your favorite.

162
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:43,720
No.

163
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,440
Give it here. I'll eat it.

164
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,240
Hey,

165
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:04,520
I still don't think they trust us.

166
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:08,760
What kind of guy
makes you guard his girlfriend

167
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:12,360
instead of letting you handle
real work or his family?

168
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,280
And if he finds out
you're not loyal to Maysa,

169
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:18,080
he can dump you anytime.

170
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,800
It's clearly a test.

171
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,600
I like games.

172
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:27,200
The harder they are, the more fun.

173
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:32,680
And I'm sure
we'll get clues about Peeraka from her.

174
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,920
SLIDE

175
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,680
You're earlier than I expected.

176
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:14,760
How could I keep you waiting, Boss?

177
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:19,240
Don't call me that.
Just call me like before.

178
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:22,280
This is just a small foundation.

179
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:27,320
And sorry for informing you so suddenly.

180
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,360
No need to apologize.

181
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:36,360
You're practically doing me a favor.

182
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:40,880
Not only does this place help victims,

183
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,080
it also launders people like me.

184
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:51,800
You said you needed security

185
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:54,320
to prevent the people
who harassed the victims

186
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,360
from harassing the foundation's work.

187
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:03,200
But in reality, you just wanted
to pull me away from protecting Ms. Maysa.

188
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,280
You think that's protecting her from me…

189
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,240
which is unnecessary.

190
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:24,360
You don't even like being near me.

191
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,960
So what is this? Kindness?

192
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:32,400
Or are you making things
harder for yourself?

193
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,160
Sounds like you want to get fired.

194
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:49,200
But I won't fire you
just for criticizing me.

195
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,920
If you don't do this job well,

196
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:59,960
you won't get a good deal
from my dad and my brother.

197
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:05,280
So do your job properly,

198
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,120
unless you want trouble.

199
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,600
Fight on.

200
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,760
You spoil Fahsai too much.

201
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:33,000
Why did you agree
to let Wayu work with her?

202
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:37,560
You know we can't trust anyone easily.

203
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:39,240
You don't trust him?

204
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,840
Yet you let him guard your girlfriend?

205
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:45,960
Hey.

206
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,960
Don't let Maysa hear that.

207
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:54,360
You're the one overprotecting Fahsai.

208
00:16:57,880 --> 00:17:01,520
Wayu wouldn't dare do anything.
He needs our connections.

209
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,760
I've thought carefully
about sending him to work with Fahsai.

210
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:12,680
Fahsai has always done what I say.

211
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:13,839
A bird

212
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:17,359
that never leaves the nest
will never grow.

213
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,480
Maybe someone like Wayu

214
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:25,000
will help your sister grow.

215
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:13,000
Do you have something to say?

216
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,960
Then why are you staring at me?

217
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:23,000
You told me to watch over you.

218
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,480
I'm just doing my job.

219
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:42,040
I'm making sure
you're never out of my sight.

220
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:50,560
Guess I'll have to deal with this
for a while…

221
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:55,640
since I took you away from May.

222
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,160
You want to stare at me?

223
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,640
Go ahead.

224
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,800
Just don't end up cross-eyed.

225
00:19:58,120 --> 00:20:00,440
The air feels so nice.

226
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,160
Do you like it?

227
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:04,320
I like it.

228
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:07,520
I'm always working, working, working.

229
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:11,080
Getting to exercise like this
feels refreshing.

230
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:15,240
I thought you wouldn't like it.

231
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:18,240
I love it.

232
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,240
It's way better than going to malls.

233
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:25,680
Thank you for taking me here.

234
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:27,160
Of course.

235
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,520
Move aside. You're blocking the way!

236
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:45,040
Hey, show some consideration
when you're riding, will you?

237
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:48,040
Do you know what could happen
if there's an accident?

238
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,800
Oh, Captain.

239
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,120
It's me.

240
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:57,200
Oh, it's you.

241
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:01,640
What a coincidence.

242
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,560
You like cycling too?

243
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,600
I do.

244
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:09,720
I should apologize
for snapping at you earlier.

245
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,000
I thought you were

246
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:15,280
one of those cyclists who buy all the gear
just to stand around taking photos.

247
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,000
Actually, Captain,

248
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:21,840
you were riding like a kid on a tricycle.

249
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:28,480
I was lost in thought for a bit,
so I wasn't fully focused.

250
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,560
I'm sorry again.

251
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:32,800
It's alright.

252
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:39,040
But when you say you weren't focused,
were you thinking about some girl?

253
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,720
Or that criminal from the other day?

254
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,880
There's still no lead.

255
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:55,800
Well, if he were that easy to catch,

256
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:58,120
they wouldn't need
a special unit like yours.

257
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,800
I'm not that good.

258
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:04,760
How about this?

259
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:07,200
If I see anyone suspicious
around the hospital again,

260
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:08,640
I'll report it right away.

261
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:11,800
Thank you.

262
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:14,360
Then let's exchange LINE.

263
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,520
Come on, let me scan your QR code.

264
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,920
What's that? QR code?

265
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,800
Your LINE QR code.

266
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:24,960
Oh, right.

267
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,160
- Is this it?
- Yes.

268
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,920
Got it, Captain.

269
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:37,840
Thank you very much.

270
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:38,800
Sure.

271
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:45,800
If anything comes up, let me know.

272
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,360
- I'll report it right away.
- Thank you.

273
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:52,360
Don't zone out again, okay?

274
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:11,840
Hey. Why is my desk like this?

275
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:19,240
There've been so many reports
about victims needing help.

276
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,360
Aren't you going to go out
and look into them?

277
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:30,320
Or did you open this foundation
just to make it look chic, like a café?

278
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:34,720
A place to sit around with your tablet,
change the scenery,

279
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,920
and hang up a sign just to build an image?

280
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:41,560
Hey!

281
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:44,120
Didn't you say
you wouldn't fire me so easily?

282
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:49,320
Just because
I criticize you a little, right?

283
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:54,840
Fine.

284
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,080
Then tomorrow, we'll go out together.

285
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,360
Thank you.

286
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:13,360
Praya, can I ask you something?

287
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,720
Do you know this police officer?

288
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,400
Why are you asking?

289
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:35,560
He came to the hospital the other day
looking for Black Doc.

290
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:37,680
He seemed very serious.

291
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:41,720
So I got close to him, just in case
it helps Wayu stay one step ahead.

292
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,120
I don't think
you should get involved in this.

293
00:25:50,080 --> 00:25:51,960
Remember what your father said?

294
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:53,880
He wants you to live a normal life.

295
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,000
Too late.

296
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:02,520
I'm his daughter.
I was never normal to begin with.

297
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:08,600
And don't you dare tell Wayu about this.

298
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,120
Before we visit the first house,

299
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:02,520
I'd like to stop by
that coffee shop ahead.

300
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:06,400
You don't mind, right?

301
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:16,800
What do you want to drink? I'll go get it.

302
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:23,120
I'm sitting in the back for safety.

303
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:27,080
And I'm fully aware

304
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:30,680
that you're not my driver or my servant.

305
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:35,120
I'll go get it myself. You want anything?

306
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:42,520
I'd like an espresso, double shot.

307
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:47,640
But can I go with you as…

308
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,360
a colleague?

309
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:54,840
Can I?

310
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:23,120
- Come here!
- Let go!

311
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:25,040
Stop struggling! Shut up!

312
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:27,160
‪-Come here!
‪-Hey!

313
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,560
- Stop!
- Let go!

314
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:30,720
She's my girlfriend. Not your business.

315
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:33,600
Even if she's your girlfriend,
you don't have the right to hurt her.

316
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:35,360
I don't hurt anyone else, just her.

317
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:37,200
So stay out of it.

318
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:39,920
- Come here!
- Let go!

319
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:43,240
- Let go of me!
- Come here.

320
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:47,840
You're only tough with women?

321
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:51,120
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

322
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,680
Hey.

323
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:57,200
I said stay out of this.

324
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:19,120
Call the police.

325
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:21,440
191, hello.

326
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,880
Miss? Miss!

327
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:30,160
PICKUP, DROP-OFF

328
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,800
How were you taking care of Fahsai?

329
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:41,640
How did she end up
in a dangerous situation like that?

330
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,760
It's not his fault.

331
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:49,240
I stepped in to stop the attacker myself.
And I'm not hurt.

332
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,280
It's just…

333
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:53,480
My condition came back.

334
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:56,280
But still,

335
00:29:56,360 --> 00:30:00,920
it's your job to protect her
from things like that.

336
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:02,760
Samut.

337
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:04,520
I already feel embarrassed enough

338
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:07,360
for fainting when no one even hurt me.

339
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:11,040
Please don't make it worse.

340
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:16,760
Fahsai,

341
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:19,560
are you really okay?

342
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:22,360
Yes.

343
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:23,960
Fahsai.

344
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:28,440
You've been in therapy for years,

345
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:30,680
and it still hasn't gone away.

346
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:34,960
Mr. Wayu,

347
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:37,880
I believe you've trained
many people before.

348
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:41,640
Do you have any way
to help Fahsai become stronger?

349
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:49,760
Dad, I think that's impossible.

350
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:53,200
Even professional therapists
couldn't do it.

351
00:30:54,320 --> 00:30:55,560
If anyone's going to teach her,

352
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:58,320
I'd rather do it myself.

353
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:00,640
You?

354
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:05,720
I know you care about her,

355
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:11,440
but caring too much

356
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:13,520
is exactly why you can't train her.

357
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:24,440
So, Mr. Wayu, do you have a way?

358
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:28,440
If you give me the chance,
I'll do my best.

359
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:31,760
Then it's settled.

360
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:53,720
We haven't even
had dinner together this week.

361
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:58,040
And Fahsai is fine now.

362
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:00,520
Can you not reschedule our date?

363
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,760
What did I tell you?

364
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:05,240
<i>Don't demand my time.</i>

365
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:06,840
You already get plenty of other things.

366
00:32:08,680 --> 00:32:12,200
I just want more time with you.

367
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:14,200
I'm sorry.

368
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:17,960
Samut,

369
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:20,560
do you have work or plans?

370
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:23,800
Don't worry about me.
If you're busy, you can go.

371
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:26,640
Don't overthink it.

372
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:28,760
It wasn't important.

373
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,240
Come on, let's go eat.

374
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,360
How's your new job?

375
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:57,360
What do you think?

376
00:32:57,880 --> 00:33:00,160
I should apologize on Fahsai's behalf.

377
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:03,640
She's still overthinking that situation,
so it made things harder for you.

378
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:08,080
Working with Ms. Fahsai isn't that hard.

379
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,280
But it's a shame.

380
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:13,520
I'd rather be working with you.

381
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:16,040
Really?

382
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:18,560
Now you're making me feel good.

383
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,960
Maybe you're just saying that
to make me happy.

384
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:26,160
Someone like you probably has someone
taking care of you all the time.

385
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:32,080
If you mean that person…

386
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:36,320
Yes, he treats me well in many ways.

387
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:38,960
But no one can give you everything.

388
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:43,560
The one thing I've never been able
to ask from him is time.

389
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:46,920
And what if I wanted that time?

390
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,400
Would that be possible?

391
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:56,320
Have dinner with me.

392
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:03,640
Why not?

393
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:12,159
But let me make a quick call first.

394
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:30,400
I'll go inside first.

395
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:32,040
Okay.

396
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,679
What now?

397
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,360
Nothing.

398
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:46,040
I just wanted to tell you
I have plans with a friend tonight.

399
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:47,760
I might be home late.

400
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:51,600
Mr. Wayu invited me to dinner here.

401
00:34:52,199 --> 00:34:55,520
Cancel it. I've already booked a table.

402
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,160
But didn't you say…

403
00:34:58,240 --> 00:35:02,160
You're the one who wanted
time with me, aren't you?

404
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:06,400
<i>If you're not going,</i>
<i>then don't ask for anything again.</i>

405
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:09,400
My secretary will send you the location.

406
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,400
I'm sorry.

407
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,120
Tonight won't work.

408
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:23,880
Can we go another time?

409
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:27,800
That's a shame.

410
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:32,480
Guess I can't really say no.

411
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,920
Alright. Another time then.

412
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:41,040
I'll get going.

413
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:42,520
Okay.

414
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:56,240
If that woman wasn't an actress,

415
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:59,360
she could switch careers
and become a mafia boss.

416
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:03,040
Cold-blooded as hell.

417
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,080
Playing with scars is not fun.

418
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:14,920
The boss already warned you.

419
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,240
It is fun.

420
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,480
The most fun.

421
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,440
The harder it gets,

422
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,680
the more I want to see

423
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:27,320
the day Mahasamut…

424
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:32,920
hits rock bottom.

425
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:36,160
And what will Maysa do?

426
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:45,760
Well, you're not completely unlucky.

427
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,840
Even though one woman poisoned you,

428
00:36:50,240 --> 00:36:52,080
there's another one risking herself,

429
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:55,640
going to Captain Anawin just to help you.

430
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:07,200
Did you try to stop her?

431
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,480
Of course.

432
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:13,400
But you know how she is.

433
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:26,960
At least Captain Anawin isn't a bad guy.

434
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:29,920
He just has a bad boss.

435
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,080
If you can't stop her,

436
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:38,600
then keep an eye on Prapai for me.

437
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:56,720
Hey.

438
00:37:58,280 --> 00:38:00,360
Weren't you the one who said
you wouldn't let me lose my job so easily?

439
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:02,800
I can't do this.

440
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,000
Hey.

441
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,200
It's not that hard.

442
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,240
Not bad.

443
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:39,360
What's there to be proud of?

444
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:42,000
Then let's try something
you can be proud of.

445
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:52,920
It's just like that pebble,

446
00:38:53,520 --> 00:38:55,720
except it has more force behind it.

447
00:38:57,720 --> 00:39:00,720
Trust me. It's not scary.

448
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,320
What are you doing? Let go.

449
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,320
It's not that scary.

450
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:22,360
Let go.

451
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:32,000
Do you think I'm a kindergarten kid?

452
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,200
Or would you rather hold a real one?

453
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:34,360
No.

454
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:40,040
I'm not messing with you.

455
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:42,880
I just want you to get used to it
step by step.

456
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,840
Don't underestimate even a toy.

457
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,160
You saw it.

458
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:50,320
Even a pebble can be a weapon
if it hits the right spot.

459
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:55,560
I'm not training you to be a shooter.

460
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:58,400
I just want you to overcome your fear.

461
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:01,120
You don't like yourself either

462
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,680
when you collapse that easily, do you?

463
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:08,920
Stop talking.

464
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:23,840
Just tell me what to do.

465
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:30,920
First, open your eyes.

466
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:34,240
Come on.

467
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,520
I'll teach you how to hold it.

468
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:50,960
Right hand grips the handle.

469
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:55,640
Left hand supports like this.

470
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:57,560
Right thumb

471
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:01,160
over the left, then aim.

472
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:06,360
Okay? Try it.

473
00:41:34,680 --> 00:41:36,400
Here he is, sir. He's one of them.

474
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:41,000
Tell me who Black Doc is.

475
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:44,160
I don't know, sir.
I've never even seen his face.

476
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:45,960
My job is to bring injured people to him.

477
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:48,200
You think I'd believe that?

478
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:54,880
I swear, sir, I don't know.

479
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:57,200
He doesn't stay in one place.

480
00:41:57,280 --> 00:42:00,280
He only shows up
when someone's seriously injured.

481
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:03,320
I just contact him, that's it.

482
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:09,680
Then you'll be the one
contacting him for me.

483
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:16,880
- Take him.
- Go!

484
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:18,160
Don't let him out of your sight.

485
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:19,280
Yes, sir.

486
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,240
Go!

487
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:23,320
Focus when you aim.

488
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:30,960
Wait for the right moment.

489
00:42:32,840 --> 00:42:34,360
Hold steady.

490
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:39,560
Then pull the trigger.

491
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:44,800
See? You can do it.

492
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:47,840
That was you, not me.

493
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:52,280
I already passed my skills to you.

494
00:43:11,160 --> 00:43:14,000
That's enough for today.
I've got something urgent.

495
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:16,640
Head back on your own. Sorry.

496
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:56,240
Sir, our man just sent
the location of Black Doc.

497
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:01,120
That illegal doctor
walked right into our trap.

498
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:02,040
BANG YAI

499
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:03,840
- Captain.
- Yes, sir.

500
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:06,360
Take the team and drag him in.

501
00:44:06,440 --> 00:44:07,480
Yes, sir!

502
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:10,080
Yes, sir.

503
00:44:12,200 --> 00:44:15,320
This time, you're finished, Black Doc.

504
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:45,520
Stop.

505
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:47,680
Police are here.

506
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:53,480
Let me finish dressing the wound.

507
00:45:14,360 --> 00:45:15,440
Hey!

508
00:45:16,480 --> 00:45:17,800
Captain.

509
00:45:17,880 --> 00:45:19,160
Everyone, get out.

510
00:45:19,760 --> 00:45:20,720
Get out.

511
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:22,840
Or he dies.

512
00:45:23,440 --> 00:45:25,920
Don't listen to him. Arrest him!

513
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:30,040
Fall back.

514
00:45:32,080 --> 00:45:33,160
Go.

515
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:36,600
Close the door. Lock it.

516
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:31,280
Captain!

517
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:09,880
Hey!

518
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:22,200
What the hell kind of operation was that?

519
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:26,160
An entire unit
and you couldn't catch one man?

520
00:47:26,240 --> 00:47:27,760
Should I transfer all of you?

521
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:31,080
He's not working alone, sir.

522
00:47:31,160 --> 00:47:33,160
He has backup.

523
00:47:35,720 --> 00:47:37,800
After all that planning
and you still failed.

524
00:47:38,720 --> 00:47:41,960
Now he'll be even more careful.

525
00:47:43,560 --> 00:47:44,880
Who's taking responsibility?

526
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:48,480
But we got his blood, sir.

527
00:47:48,560 --> 00:47:50,760
If we send it for DNA analysis,

528
00:47:50,840 --> 00:47:52,480
we might still have a lead.

529
00:47:54,800 --> 00:47:56,240
Send it immediately.

530
00:47:56,320 --> 00:47:58,600
Report as soon as you have results.

531
00:47:59,240 --> 00:48:00,160
Yes, sir.

532
00:48:23,360 --> 00:48:24,560
Okay.

533
00:48:40,240 --> 00:48:41,760
Let me dress it.

534
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:48,720
You need to be more careful.

535
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:52,920
You can't just go out
treating people like that anymore.

536
00:48:53,520 --> 00:48:54,760
We can't trust anyone…

537
00:48:56,760 --> 00:48:58,160
not even our own.

538
00:49:00,280 --> 00:49:02,080
So when did you become my stalker?

539
00:49:03,160 --> 00:49:04,520
You're following me everywhere?

540
00:49:06,720 --> 00:49:07,880
It's my job.

541
00:49:10,160 --> 00:49:12,200
I have to protect
both of the boss's children.

542
00:49:12,720 --> 00:49:13,960
Thanks.

543
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:35,240
Isn't Mr. Wayu coming in today?

544
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:39,600
Good. Better if he doesn't.

545
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:40,880
Wait a second.

546
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:42,640
Where are you going?

547
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:46,320
I'm going to visit the woman
who was abused at the mall.

548
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:49,400
Wait, please. Wait for Mr. Wayu too.

549
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,240
- I'll call him.
- No, it's fine.

550
00:49:51,320 --> 00:49:53,480
I can go by myself.

551
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:55,120
It's better that way.

552
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:57,080
There won't be someone
there to get on my nerves.

553
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:58,240
- Oh.
- I'm off.

554
00:49:58,320 --> 00:49:59,880
You can't, Ms. Fahsai.

555
00:49:59,960 --> 00:50:02,120
Wait, please.

556
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:04,040
My gosh. What should I do?

557
00:50:46,240 --> 00:50:47,480
Where did you hide my girl?

558
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:51,760
Tell me! Where did you hide her?

559
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:02,400
Get out.

560
00:51:02,480 --> 00:51:04,000
Get out!

561
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:06,040
If you don't,

562
00:51:07,160 --> 00:51:08,440
I'll shoot you.

563
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:11,280
Hurry!

564
00:51:15,760 --> 00:51:17,640
Tell me where you hid my girlfriend!

565
00:51:17,720 --> 00:51:20,000
Please don't do this. This is wrong.

566
00:51:20,080 --> 00:51:21,840
- Let go of me.
- I won't.

567
00:51:21,920 --> 00:51:23,880
Not until you tell me
where my girlfriend is.

568
00:51:24,840 --> 00:51:26,240
Let go!

569
00:51:35,080 --> 00:51:36,960
If you're going to keep your mouth shut,

570
00:51:37,040 --> 00:51:39,680
then choose, your life or hers.

571
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:42,320
So?

572
00:51:50,840 --> 00:51:52,240
Are you alright?

573
00:51:53,120 --> 00:51:54,840
Are you alright? Calm down.

574
00:51:55,480 --> 00:51:56,480
- Breathe.
- Watch out.

575
00:52:30,840 --> 00:52:32,120
Get the gun!

576
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:34,200
I can't.

577
00:52:34,280 --> 00:52:35,880
Get the gun now!

578
00:52:36,520 --> 00:52:37,480
Get the gun!

579
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:45,720
Get the gun.

580
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:47,440
Get the gun!

581
00:52:50,120 --> 00:52:51,200
Get the gun.

582
00:52:56,800 --> 00:52:58,080
Aim.

583
00:52:58,800 --> 00:52:59,800
Aim.

584
00:53:00,400 --> 00:53:01,440
Aim!

585
00:53:03,160 --> 00:53:05,160
Shoot. Shoot!

586
00:53:11,520 --> 00:53:12,960
Are you alright?

587
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:44,120
How could you let something like this
happen to my daughter?

588
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:49,240
If you had been even a second later,
Fahsai would be dead.

589
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:51,360
If you want me to take responsibility,

590
00:53:52,120 --> 00:53:53,120
I will.

591
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:56,600
If you want to fire me,

592
00:53:57,160 --> 00:53:59,400
I have no right to argue,

593
00:54:00,200 --> 00:54:01,760
because I was at fault.

594
00:54:03,840 --> 00:54:05,000
Fire you?

595
00:54:07,760 --> 00:54:09,280
Who would fire you?

596
00:54:11,880 --> 00:54:14,760
You made Fahsai dare to hold a gun.

597
00:54:18,080 --> 00:54:18,920
No.

598
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:23,600
She fired it.

599
00:54:26,560 --> 00:54:28,440
You made her stronger.

600
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:31,280
Should I fire you?

601
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:37,520
I should reward you instead.

602
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:41,800
<i>Following the shocking attack</i>
<i>on Ms. Fahsai,</i>

603
00:54:41,880 --> 00:54:44,680
<i>daughter of Minister Rakchart,</i>

604
00:54:44,760 --> 00:54:46,680
<i>the public has been outraged.</i>

605
00:54:46,760 --> 00:54:50,320
<i>Fortunately, her bodyguard</i>
<i>arrived just in time to save her.</i>

606
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:53,880
Come in.

607
00:54:59,800 --> 00:55:01,880
Black Doc's DNA results, sir.

608
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:05,000
We compared the DNA

609
00:55:05,080 --> 00:55:08,680
against all known criminal records.
No match.

610
00:55:10,920 --> 00:55:12,840
Right now, all we have is the DNA.

611
00:55:13,560 --> 00:55:17,240
We'll need to identify
new suspects for comparison.

612
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:22,760
Keep searching.

613
00:55:23,880 --> 00:55:25,480
Now that we have the DNA,

614
00:55:25,560 --> 00:55:27,560
things should get easier.

615
00:55:29,240 --> 00:55:31,240
If you suspect anyone, issue a summons.

616
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:33,040
Yes, sir.

617
00:55:35,400 --> 00:55:38,080
<i>The suspect was shot in a major artery</i>

618
00:55:38,160 --> 00:55:41,320
<i>in the thigh, causing severe bleeding.</i>

619
00:55:41,400 --> 00:55:44,520
<i>However, he survived thanks to</i>
<i>the assistance of Ms. Fahsai's bodyguard,</i>

620
00:55:44,600 --> 00:55:47,200
<i>later identified as Mr. Wayu Buranachat.</i>

621
00:56:01,800 --> 00:56:02,920
Sir.

622
00:56:03,440 --> 00:56:05,400
The last time I pursued Black Doc,

623
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:07,640
he escaped into an animal hospital.

624
00:56:08,280 --> 00:56:12,080
I searched the place. Nothing suspicious.

625
00:56:12,160 --> 00:56:14,240
I saw it in your report.

626
00:56:16,360 --> 00:56:18,840
But the owner's name

627
00:56:18,920 --> 00:56:21,360
is Prapai Buranachat.

628
00:56:24,080 --> 00:56:25,680
Mr. Wayu's younger sister.

629
00:56:31,960 --> 00:56:35,560
<i>Footage from CCTV and Mr. Wayu's dashcam</i>

630
00:56:35,640 --> 00:56:38,320
<i>showed him saving the suspect's life.</i>

631
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:40,320
<i>Social media users praised</i>

632
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:43,440
<i>his professional first aid.</i>

633
00:56:44,120 --> 00:56:46,560
<i>Some even suspect he might be a doctor.</i>

634
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:49,920
He really does look like a doctor.

635
00:57:04,120 --> 00:57:05,720
Ms. Fahsai, you know,

636
00:57:05,800 --> 00:57:09,120
last night was the first time
I've slept peacefully

637
00:57:09,800 --> 00:57:12,000
since Nick started abusing me.

638
00:57:12,080 --> 00:57:14,680
Even when I ran away,

639
00:57:14,760 --> 00:57:16,600
I could never sleep.

640
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:19,560
I really

641
00:57:20,360 --> 00:57:22,440
have to thank you.

642
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:27,240
I still can't believe
we caught him either.

643
00:57:30,320 --> 00:57:32,160
I was terrified too.

644
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:37,600
But if I could get through it, so can you.

645
00:57:38,840 --> 00:57:40,560
We'll get through this.

646
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:43,400
Yes.

647
00:58:04,920 --> 00:58:06,080
You…

648
00:58:15,280 --> 00:58:17,640
I never even got the chance

649
00:58:26,280 --> 00:58:28,160
to thank you properly.

650
00:58:29,440 --> 00:58:30,400
You?

651
00:58:32,920 --> 00:58:34,320
Who is she talking about?

652
00:58:34,880 --> 00:58:36,720
I haven't forgotten

653
00:58:36,800 --> 00:58:40,280
what I told you that when I get better

654
00:58:41,520 --> 00:58:43,040
and stronger,

655
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:47,760
I'll prove the truth about you.

656
00:58:58,040 --> 00:59:00,280
Why is she talking like this
in the middle of the night?

657
00:59:02,040 --> 00:59:03,200
And she won't stop.

658
00:59:06,200 --> 00:59:07,320
Is she sleep-talking or what?

659
00:59:43,480 --> 00:59:44,720
Checkmate.

660
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:52,040
I shouldn't have taught you.

661
00:59:52,120 --> 00:59:54,000
You beat me every time.

662
01:00:03,320 --> 01:00:05,120
- Yeah?
- Bro.

663
01:00:05,640 --> 01:00:07,560
Did you check Ms. Fahsai's location?

664
01:00:07,640 --> 01:00:09,080
I check it all the time.

665
01:00:09,160 --> 01:00:10,000
Are you sure?

666
01:00:10,080 --> 01:00:11,200
Alright, fine.

667
01:00:11,280 --> 01:00:12,760
I was playing chess with Praya.

668
01:00:13,600 --> 01:00:14,720
I knew it.

669
01:00:15,240 --> 01:00:17,520
Do you even know
where Ms. Fahsai is going right now?

670
01:00:24,840 --> 01:00:27,560
The Jaiaree family case
was closed six years ago.

671
01:00:27,640 --> 01:00:30,040
What do you want to know about this case?

672
01:00:30,120 --> 01:00:32,360
<i>Just because we're in different parties</i>

673
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:33,800
<i>doesn't mean we can't work together.</i>

674
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:36,120
What the hell is this supposed to mean?

675
01:00:36,200 --> 01:00:37,480
Your apology

676
01:00:37,560 --> 01:00:40,000
means nothing anymore.

677
01:00:40,600 --> 01:00:41,720
You're dismissed.

678
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:42,920
I have something for you to do.

679
01:00:44,320 --> 01:00:46,880
Good afternoon, sir.

680
01:00:46,960 --> 01:00:48,600
That man, Wayu…

681
01:00:49,400 --> 01:00:51,240
I want to test something about him.

682
01:00:52,360 --> 01:00:53,440
How is it?

683
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:55,120
Just as beautiful as I imagined.

684
01:00:55,200 --> 01:00:56,960
Do you need any help?

685
01:00:57,040 --> 01:00:58,680
Let me just touch up my makeup for a bit.

686
01:01:02,960 --> 01:01:04,440
The DNA results, sir.

687
01:02:03,800 --> 01:02:05,800
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
